text.section:
The Department may promulgate rules and regulations relating to any aspect of the soft-shell clam fishery and shall adopt rules and regulations governing:
Measurement and structural details of a hydraulic clam dredge;
The number of hydraulic clam dredges which may be carried on a vessel;
The use of mufflers on motors or engines on hydraulic clam dredges or on board boats carrying hydraulic clam dredges;
The establishment of limits on the number of bushels which may be caught by a hydraulic clam dredge, or by a boat carrying a hydraulic clam dredge;
The minimum size of soft-shell clams;
The times and dates for taking, landing, and unloading soft-shell clams; and
Protection of soft-shell clams from contamination, or from deterioration as a result of excessive heat.
